# Per-stream credentials for SLS. Consumed via the `user_file` directive.
#
# USAGE:
#   1. Copy this file:  cp sls-users.conf.example sls-users.conf
#   2. Edit sls-users.conf with real passphrases (see the format below).
#   3. sls-users.conf is .gitignore'd so local edits stay out of commits.
#   4. Point `user_file` in your SLS config at sls-users.conf.
#
# FORMAT (one user per line, whitespace-separated):
#   <stream_name>  <publish_pass>  <play_pass>
#
# A passphrase of "-" means "no passphrase for that direction; plaintext
# connection allowed." Stream names not listed here are rejected at the
# SRT handshake stage.
#
# Passphrases must be 10-79 printable ASCII characters (libsrt limit).
#
# The three examples below illustrate every combination:
#   - alice:       fully private -- encrypted push AND encrypted pull.
#   - bob_public:  authenticated streamer, open (plaintext) viewers.
#   - carol_open:  anyone can push, viewers need the key. (Unusual.)
#
# All placeholder values contain "EXAMPLE" and are NOT safe to deploy.
#
# name         publish_pass                   play_pass
alice          alice-publish-EXAMPLE-key      alice-play-EXAMPLE-key
bob_public     bob-publish-EXAMPLE-key        -
carol_open     -                              carol-play-EXAMPLE-key
